{"id":1134202159,"question_id":2724,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"5 months, 1 week","timestamp":1704161315,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"4 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1134202159/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Convert an Array Into a 2D Array With Conditions","memory":"45 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public List<List<Integer>> findMatrix(int[] nums) {\n        List<List<Integer>> res = new ArrayList<>();\n\n        int len = nums.length;\n\n        int cnt = 0;\n        boolean[] seen = new boolean[len];\n\n        while(cnt<len){\n            List<Integer> list = new ArrayList<>();\n            for(int i=0; i<len ; i++){\n\n                if(!list.contains(nums[i]) && !seen[i]){\n                    list.add(nums[i]);\n                    seen[i]=true;\n                    cnt++;\n                }\n            }    \n            res.add(new ArrayList<>(list));\n        }\n\n        return res;\n\n        \n        \n\n\n         \n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"convert-an-array-into-a-2d-array-with-conditions","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
